text:
For the confused shork as well as many others who don't understand "Brawl reference:"

In Super Smash Brothers Brawl for the Wii, the team had introduced a mechanic where you can trip through various means. The infamous one happens from you starting a dash. This was done to give the competitive smash scene a figurative middle finger since dash dancing is a vital movement option, so there's a chance you get punished for dashing. Tripping stayed, but the team took out the random element of it for the future titles, so only certain attacks can cause it.

Brawl is a black sheep of the series because a lot of it's design choices was done to screw the competitive scene over, and the game suffered for it. The team at the time was hellbent on ruining the scene because it was meant to be a simple party game, and nothing else. I think it being an ESport had something to do with it too? Whatever the case, it's still an amazing game with the best story mode though!

The creator of the series, PuffballsUnited, wanted to release one last gigantic update to the series as his final thank you to the fans before ending the Henry Stickmin series. That was completing the mission. And he announced that it would be released on steam fairly early into development. Thankfully he added in all of the other ones so that everyone can enjoy the full experience even with flash dying. But this is sadly the final update to the Henry Stickmin series.
